<% content_for :title do %>SMS & voice | <%= installation_brand_name %> User Guide<% end %>
<% content_for :meta_description do %>Connect SMS and voice channels in <%= installation_brand_name %> via Twilio, Bandwidth, and voice inboxes.<% end %>

<h1>SMS & voice</h1>
<p class="lead">
  Text and call customers through telephony providers integrated as <%= installation_brand_name %> inboxes.
</p>

<h2>Twilio SMS</h2>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Settings → Inboxes → Add inbox → SMS → Twilio</strong></li>
  <li>Enter Twilio Account SID and Auth Token</li>
  <li>Select or enter the Twilio phone number</li>
  <li>Configure webhook URL in Twilio console if not auto-set</li>
  <li>Send test SMS to the number; reply from dashboard</li>
</ol>

<h2>Bandwidth SMS</h2>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Add inbox → SMS → Bandwidth</strong></li>
  <li>Enter Bandwidth API credentials and application ID</li>
  <li>Map phone number and webhook</li>
</ol>

<h2>Voice calls</h2>
<p>Voice inboxes (Twilio voice) allow inbound/outbound phone support:</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Add inbox → Voice</strong></li>
  <li>Connect Twilio voice credentials and number</li>
  <li>Configure call flow (ring agents, voicemail, etc.) per inbox settings</li>
</ol>
<p>Agent experience and availability depend on your plan and installation configuration.</p>

<h2>WhatsApp via Twilio</h2>
<p>Some setups use Twilio as WhatsApp BSP instead of embedded Meta signup. Follow the WhatsApp + Twilio option in inbox creation if shown.</p>

<h2>SMS campaigns</h2>
<p>Send proactive SMS via <a href="<%= guide_page_path('campaigns') %>">SMS campaigns</a>. Respect opt-in and local telecom regulations (TCPA, GDPR, etc.).</p>

<h2>Compliance</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Obtain consent before marketing SMS</li>
  <li>Include opt-out instructions where required</li>
  <li>Do not send sensitive data over SMS unless policy allows</li>
</ul>

<h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Inbound SMS missing — verify webhook URL and Twilio/Bandwidth number config</li>
  <li>Outbound fails — check account balance, number capabilities, geographic permissions</li>
  <li><a href="<%= guide_page_path('troubleshooting') %>">General troubleshooting</a></li>
</ul>

